Mobile App Security Analysis - Android Focus [25M]
PART 1: Analysis Commands & Checklist [10M]
Setup & Tools Installation
bash
# Install Required Tools
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk android-sdk-platform-tools -y

# Install APKTool
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/iBotPeaches/Apktool/master/scripts/linux/apktool
chmod +x apktool
sudo mv apktool /usr/local/bin/

# Install JADX
wget https://github.com/skylot/jadx/releases/download/v1.4.7/jadx-gui-1.4.7.zip
unzip jadx-gui-1.4.7.zip
cd jadx-gui-1.4.7 && ./jadx-gui

# Install Frida
pip3 install frida-tools objection
1. Static Analysis
bash
# Decompile APK
apktool d target.apk -o decompiled/
jadx target.apk -d java_source/

# Check AndroidManifest.xml
cd decompiled/
cat AndroidManifest.xml

# Critical Checks:
echo "=== Critical Vulnerabilities ==="
grep "android:debuggable=\"true\"" AndroidManifest.xml
grep "android:allowBackup=\"true\"" AndroidManifest.xml  
grep "android:usesCleartextTraffic=\"true\"" AndroidManifest.xml
grep "android:exported=\"true\"" AndroidManifest.xml

# List all permissions
grep "uses-permission" AndroidManifest.xml

# Search hardcoded secrets
cd ../java_source/
grep -r "API_KEY\|SECRET\|PASSWORD\|TOKEN\|KEY" . --include="*.java"
grep -r "http://" . --include="*.xml" --include="*.java"
2. Dynamic Analysis
bash
# Connect device/emulator
adb devices
adb install target.apk

# Get app package name
adb shell pm list packages | grep -i "appname"

# Monitor logs for sensitive data
adb logcat | grep -iE "password|token|key|secret|credit|pin"

# Monitor specific app
adb logcat | grep "$(adb shell ps | grep com.example.app | awk '{print $2}')"

# Check app data storage
adb shell
run-as com.example.app
ls -la /data/data/com.example.app/
cat /data/data/com.example.app/shared_prefs/*.xml
ls /data/data/com.example.app/databases/

# Check SQLite databases
sqlite3 /data/data/com.example.app/databases/app.db
.tables
SELECT * FROM sensitive_table;
3. Network Analysis
bash
# Setup Burp Suite proxy
# 1. Start Burp: Proxy → Options → Add 127.0.0.1:8080
# 2. Configure Android emulator:
adb shell settings put global http_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080

# Install Burp certificate
# Download from http://burp/cert
adb push burp.crt /sdcard/
adb shell
su
cp /sdcard/burp.crt /system/etc/security/cacerts/
chmod 644 /system/etc/security/cacerts/burp.crt
reboot
4. Runtime Analysis with Frida
bash
# Install Frida server
adb root
adb push frida-server /data/local/tmp/
adb shell chmod 755 /data/local/tmp/frida-server
adb shell /data/local/tmp/frida-server &

# List running apps
frida-ps -U

# Trace app
frida-trace -U -i "open" com.example.app

# Bypass SSL Pinning
objection -g com.example.app explore
android sslpinning disable

# Inside objection console:
android hooking list classes
android hooking search classes password
android hooking watch class_method com.example.app.LoginActivity.onLogin --dump-args
android storage list shared_prefs
5. Common Vulnerability Checklist
#	Vulnerability	Check Command	Severity
1	Debuggable enabled	grep debuggable AndroidManifest.xml	High
2	AllowBackup enabled	grep allowBackup AndroidManifest.xml	Medium
3	HTTP traffic	grep usesCleartextTraffic AndroidManifest.xml	High
4	Exported components	grep -c "exported=\"true\"" AndroidManifest.xml	High
5	Hardcoded secrets	grep -r "API_KEY|SECRET" java_source/	Critical
6	Insecure logging	adb logcat | grep password	Medium
7	Weak encryption	grep -r "AES|RSA|DES" java_source/	High
8	SQL Injection	grep -r "rawQuery|execSQL" java_source/	High
9	Missing certificate pinning	grep -r "HostnameVerifier|TrustManager" java_source/	High
10	Intent injection	grep -r "getIntent().get" java_source/	Medium
